<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Monica's Main Street merchants have elected a new chairman to oversee 
business publicity on the popular thoroughfare. 
</P>
<P>
 David Teck, owner of the World Cafe restaurant, will serve as chairman of the 
Santa Monica Main Street Assessment Board. The board is a group of merchants 
who determine and create publicity programs for Main Street in coordination 
with the city and Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 Teck and the board are preparing for the trial run of a Main Street farmers' 
market that is due to open Monday. 
