<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIVIC CENTER: A MISLEADING DISPUTE OVER HEIGHT LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laurel Roennau's recent letter to The Times (Westside section, Aug. 4) 
presents an inaccurate view of council member Kelly Olsen's actions regarding 
the Civic Center. She bases her conclusions on an assertion that he presented a 
motion to the City Council which ultimately permitted increased maximum heights 
in the proposed RAND developments on Ocean Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Council member Olsen's motion did not raise the maximum permitted heights as 
stated in the Specific Plan by 14 feet, as Ms. Roennau claims. In fact, council 
member Olsen's motion lowered the maximum permitted heights by 14 feet, or one 
full story. 
</P>
<P>
 We are the entire membership of the Civic Center working group, which was 
appointed by the City Council. Our mission was to facilitate a process to reach 
a community consensus on the urban design plan for the Civic Center. We 
recognize Ms. Roennau's right to her opinion of council member Olsen. However, 
her facts are incorrect. 
</P>
<P>
 KEN GENSER and PAUL ROSENSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
 City Council members Santa Monica  
</P>
<P>
 RALPH MECHUR, PAM O'CONNOR and ERIC PARLEE 
