575 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOPTALK; SAVINGS AND SELECTION ABOUND FOR THE BACK-TO-SCHOOL CROWD; SALES AT 
AREA MALLS INCLUDE EVERYTHING FROM SHOES TO BACKPACKS, DENIM TO CALCULATORS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEO SMITH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you'd "rather be saling" -- to quote an old bumper sticker -- then head to 
Ventura County malls. 
</P>
<P>
 What we found when we staked out the malls recently were not only 
back-to-school sales but also fall preview sales, summer clearance sales, plain 
old sale sales, and a bunch of other reasons for marking down prices. Let's 
just say it was kind of a bargain hunter's paradise. 
</P>
<P>
 But amid all that, we did try our best to stick to our goal of locating 
merchandise specifically on sale, or prominently displayed, as back-to-school 
stuff. 
</P>
<P>
 We went to The Oaks in Thousand Oaks, the Esplanade in Oxnard and the 
Buenaventura Mall in Ventura. And here's what we found. Keep in mind that 
sales, and available stock, come and go pretty quickly this time of year. 
</P>
<P>
 First stop, The Oaks. What impressed us there was an abundance of 
nice-looking, quality backpacks for school. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller's Outpost had a Jansport backpack sale scheduled to last through 
Saturday. We found a regularly priced $30 nylon pack marked down 40%, and a $45 
nylon-suede pack discounted 20%. (The Miller's Outpost at the Buenaventura Mall 
had 20% off all Jansport packs.) 
</P>
<P>
 The largest selection of backpacks at The Oaks was at Oshman's Sporting Goods 
store, though the prices were somewhat higher in the Jansport models. The store 
had a nice supply of Eastpak packs, with the lowest priced at $29.99. Oshman's, 
by the way, has a random drawing contest for a "year's supply" (limit five 
pairs) of shoes for your child. Deadline to enter is Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Speaking of shoes, over at the Stride Rite shoe store they have a sale on 
sizes 5 to about 8, with most pairs tagged for $19.95-$24.95, $10-$15 off the 
usual price. 
</P>
<P>
 And the 5-7-9 shop (also found at The Esplanade) has a 40%-off sale on girls 
clothes (sizes 0-9) scheduled to last through the end of this week. 
</P>
<P>
 On to the Buenaventura Mall. We were pretty excited to find a back-to-school 
sale at Footaction USA, with prices cut 20% to 40% on name-brand shoes like 
Nike and Reebok. We found a pair of Nike Airs for $49.88, down from $84.99. 
This sale is supposed to last through Sept. 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps our favorite sale of the mall tour was at Radio Shack, which has 
outlets at all three malls. The store offers back-to-school electronics 
packages for elementary, high school and college students. 
</P>
<P>
 The "L-M-N-tary Pack" includes a pencil box/calculator, a cordless pencil 
sharpener, an AM/FM radio with earphone, four C batteries, and two AA 
batteries. It sells for $25, instead of the $30.85 if the items were sold 
separately. 
</P>
<P>
 Finally, we dropped in at The Esplanade, where the highlight last week was a 
25% to 50% off sale on a variety of clothing at Kids Mart. We hesitate to 
mention that because the sale is over. But we were told that this week you can 
expect a discount on denim items. 
</P>
<P>
 As for school accessories, the Payless ShoeSource (also at the Buenaventura 
Mall) had a cute little plastic Crayola Carry Bag, with four Crayola crayons, 
discounted from $7.99 to $5 -- not earth shattering, but cute. 
</P>
<P>
 And in all this mall talk let's not forget that J.C. Penney (The Oaks, 
Buenaventura) and Sears (The Oaks, Esplanade) will be having back-to-school 
sales throughout the month. 
</P>
<P>
 We realize that getting your kids ready for school may seem more daunting than 
it was to attend school yourself. Next week we hope to alleviate some of that 
pain by comparing prices on school essentials like notebooks, pencil bags and 
lunch boxes. 
</P>
