<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CERRITOS; PANEL OKS TENTATIVE TRACT MAP FOR PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JILL GOTTESMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ABC Unified School District and an Orange County developer last week 
cleared the first of several hurdles required to begin construction on a gated 
residential community on 13 acres of district land next to Whitney High School. 
 
</P>
<P>
 The planning commission recently approved a tentative tract map to create 61 
residential lots on the land. 
</P>
<P>
 The school district last year entered into a partnership with Costa Mesa-based 
Warmington Homes to develop the land to raise money for repairs and 
construction of classrooms. District officials have said they hope to receive 
$7.7 million from the deal, which includes payment for the land and a 
percentage of the profits from the homes once they are sold.  
</P>
<P>
 Those profits could be somewhat diminished, however, since the developer was 
asked by the city recently to increase the size of the lots and include more 
space between homes. The original proposal consisted of 66 lots. 
</P>
<P>
 Preliminary plans for the residential community include four floor plans, each 
encompassing 2,500 to 2,700 square feet. The developers said they hope to sell 
the homes for $350,000 to $375,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The tract map must be approved by the city council, which will take up the 
issue at its Aug. 18 meeting. The planning commission and council also must 
approve specific design plans for the homes.  
</P>
<P>
 City officials said the first homes could be completed by the end of 1995. 
JILL GOTTESMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
