<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PORT OF LOS ANGELES; OFFICIAL PROMISES TO EXPEDITE PARKS 
PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harbor Commissioner Steven L. Soboroff, who is expected to move to the 
Recreation and Parks Commission, has pledged to ensure that parks and 
recreation projects in the harbor area begin quickly. 
</P>
<P>
 Soboroff, who attended his final harbor board meeting last month, said more 
than $8 million has been allocated in Proposition A funds for harbor projects. 
</P>
<P>
 They include: Harbor Walkway ($2.7 million); the Imperial Courts Recreational 
Center Community Building ($2 million); Cabrillo Pier ($1 million); Nickerson 
Gardens building refurbishment ($750,000). 
</P>
<P>
 Also, Cabrillo Museum ($650,000); Nickerson Gardens Park redevelopment 
($500,000); the Watts Senior Citizens Center ($500,000); Daniels Field park 
redevelopment ($115,000), and Daniels Field building refurbishment ($80,000). 
SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
