<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MONTEREY PARK; CITY WORKERS PICKET FOR CONTRACT, 1% RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City employees picketed in front of Monterey Park City Hall on Tuesday to 
demand a contract and a 1% pay raise retroactive to July, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 The workers, who include all blue-collar, clerical and police department 
civilians, are represented by Service Employees International Union, Local 347, 
and have been working without a contract for two years, according to union 
negotiator Julie Butcher. 
</P>
<P>
 Butcher said the two parties are less than $100,000 apart on negotiations. But 
she said that a settlement has been stalled by city officials for various 
reasons, including passage of the state budget and municipal elections. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
