<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: LONG BEACH WOMAN TO HEAD LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Long Beach resident Mary Ann Hutton has been named senior librarian of the 
Westminster branch of the Orange County Public Library. Hutton had been head of 
the library's Mission Viejo branch. She holds a bachelor's degree in history 
from Cal State Long Beach and a master's degree in library science from USC. 
She was a librarian at Paramount Television Studios and the Huntington Beach 
Public Library. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Two sheriff's deputies from the Lakewood division have received 10851 Awards 
from the Automobile Club of Southern California. Deputies Paul Jernigan and 
Scott Anger were honored for stopping suspects in stolen vehicles. The 10851 
Award is named for the California Vehicle Code section that prohibits vehicle 
theft. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach physician Timothy Schwab was elected president of the California 
Society of Internal Medicine. Schwab, medical director of SCAN Health Plan in 
Long Beach, is also an assistant clinical professor of medicine at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Memorial Medical Center's Memorial Health Services division named 
John Hancock chairman of the board of directors. Hancock, senior vice president 
of the Bancap Investment Group, previously served as the board's vice chairman. 
Memorial Health Services provides health and managed care services. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Legal Aid Foundation of Long Beach recently honored two attorneys. The 
Sommelier d'Esprit award for distinguished service to the profession and to the 
community went to Allan E. Tebbetts, a civil rights and political attorney. The 
Leadership Challenge Award went to Norman R. Samuelsen, a retired specialist in 
worker's compensation law. The Legal Aid Foundation serves Southeast Los 
Angeles and the South Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gopal Raman was named dean of admissions and records at Long Beach City 
College. Gopal was director of admissions and financial aid for more than a 
decade at College of the Desert in Palm Desert. 
</P>
<P>
 Material for this column may be sent to People, Los Angeles Times, 12750 
Center Court, Suite 150, Cerritos 90703. (310) 924-8600.  
</P>
