<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; CHILD CARE: YMCA OPENS CORPORATE FACILITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The YMCA opened its first corporate child care facility in the South Bay this 
month at the TRW Data Technology Division in Carson. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gardena/Carson YMCA will operate the preschool for children ages 2 to 5 
whose parents work at TRW. 
</P>
<P>
 The school has about 2,000 square feet of space, including an outdoor play 
area and two classrooms. Currently 16 children attend, but the school can 
accommodate up to 50. It is open from 6:30 a.m. to 7 p.m.  
</P>
<P>
 TRW provided the facility on its property and the YMCA operates it on a 
contract. Tuition of $80 a week, paid by the families, covers the costs of 
operation, YMCA officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The YMCA will probably participate in more corporate child care centers 
because other companies in the South Bay have expressed interest in having 
quality child care available to their employees, said YMCA spokesman George 
Saikali. MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
