<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: AVALON: PUBLIC HEARING WILL FOCUS ON PROPOSAL FOR $100-MILLION 
RESORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A $100-million resort has been proposed for Santa Catalina Island. 
</P>
<P>
 Catalina G.B.C. Ltd. Partnership, a development partnership formed by The 
Pointe Group in Arizona, has leased several acres of land from the Santa 
Catalina Island Co. to build a 300-suite hotel, City Manager Robert F. Clark 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 If it gets City Council approval, the hotel will be erected on Descanso Beach, 
between the Casino building and Hamilton Cove, Clark said. 
</P>
<P>
 The development would contribute hotel and property taxes to the island 
community. 
</P>
<P>
 "That will allow the city to provide more services to the community. We're 
talking millions of dollars a year," Clark said. 
</P>
<P>
 It is hoped the hotel will attract visitors in the off-tourist season, 
especially people who can use the casino building for conventions. 
</P>
<P>
 Clark said the developer also plans to lease the Catalina Island Golf Club and 
expand it to 18 holes. 
</P>
<P>
 The council will hold a public meeting on the development plan Tuesday in 
Avalon's Los Angeles County Courthouse at 7 p.m. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
