<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Louis-based Interco Inc. said it is considering spinning off all or part 
of its Converse and Florsheim footwear divisions. An evaluation of the move is 
expected to be completed by the end of the month. . . . Armco Inc., a 
Pittsburgh-based steelmaker, said it signed a definitive agreement to sell its 
insurance businesses for about $85 million to Vik Brothers Insurance Inc., a 
privately held company in Raleigh, N.C. . . . The Defense Department said Japan 
wants to buy two airborne early-warning systems built by Boeing Co. at a total 
estimated cost of $547 million. The sale of the systems is expected to be 
unopposed by Congress. . . . Eli Lilly & Co. announced that it is extending its 
offer to purchase all common shares outstanding of McKesson Corp. for $76.00 
per share in cash until 5 p.m., EDT, Sept. 9. 
</P>
