 "We're not going to eliminate foul play at this time, but all indications 
point to an embezzlement theft by Misty and her boyfriend," Las Vegas Metro 
Police Lt. Mike Hawkins said Wednesday. "The speculation is that they have left 
the state." 
</P>
<P>
 The armored truck was found abandoned Tuesday night in an empty unit of a 
warehouse complex a short distance from where the vehicle disappeared hours 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkins said "a few thousand dollars, mostly in change," was found inside the 
truck. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkins said authorities believe that the crime is an embezzlement because 
there were no signs of foul play or a struggle in the armored truck and because 
of "other indicators that we can't go into now." 
</P>
<P>
 Smith was last seen by another Brinks guard inside the truck minutes before 
the disappearance, which took place just before noon Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
