<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: SELBE TO COACH AT CYPRESS AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Selbe is returning as football coach at Cypress High, replacing Jack 
Jensen, who become an assistant coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Selbe, also the school's athletic director, was the Centurion coach for eight 
seasons, from 1985-92.He had a 24-43-3 record during that time. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The defending champion Bullfrogs will open the 1994 Roller Hockey 
International playoffs on the road at San Jose next Thursday, the team said 
Wednesday. ESPN2 will broadcast the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The second game of the home-away series will be Aug. 19 at 7:30 p.m. at The 
Pond of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the home game will be $6, $12 and $25, and will be available 
weekdays beginning Friday at The Pond box office and Ticketmaster outlets. 
</P>
<P>
 If the series is split after two games, a 12-minute "mini-game" will follow to 
determine the winner. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Former Tustin High pitcher Brian Helsper has signed a letter of intent to play 
baseball at San Jose State, Tustin Coach Tim O'Donoghue said. 
</P>
<P>
 Helsper was 7-1 for the Tillers last season and was named to the All-Sea View 
League first team. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 SoCal of Tustin advanced three teams to the semifinals of the national Junior 
Olympic water polo championships at Long Beach State. Goalie Ryan Brown of 
Foothill High had nine saves to lead the 17-and-older team to an 11-4 victory 
over Commerce. Brian Brown of Foothill had five goals to lead the 
15-and-younger team to an 8-7 victory over Concord. The SoCal 13-and-younger 
team also advanced to the semifinals, scheduled for Friday morning at Long 
Beach State. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar's 13-under team lost to Long Beach Wilson, 10-4, at Wilson and 
was eliminated from the championship bracket. 
</P>
</TEXT>
