<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SCHOOL DISTRICT ISSUES DRESS CODE REMINDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westminster School District officials are urging parents to buy back-to-school 
clothing for their children that adheres to the district's dress code, a 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 District policy forbids any clothing that presents a health, safety or 
discipline problem.Prohibited items include cutoff pants and "immodest" shorts, 
as well as hats, caps, bandannas and tank tops. Other clothing not permitted 
includes shirts with obscene writing, suggestive words and inappropriate 
product advertisements, spokeswoman Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The district also prohibits all clothing associated with gangs, such as Los 
Angeles Kings or Los Angeles Raiders attire, baggy pants with white or striped 
T-shirts and overalls worn with straps hanging off the shoulders, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Even if children are not affiliated with a gang, their clothes can be 
misinterpreted, and that can be dangerous. If there is any question, children 
need to change their clothes," Supt. Gail Wickstrom said. 
</P>
<P>
 School officials may send children home if they are wearing inappropriate 
attire, Brown said.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
