<P>
 U.S. Imposes Ban on Taiwan Wildlife: The import ban on fish and wildlife 
products, established because of the country's failure to halt trafficking in 
tiger bones and rhino horns, will go into effect Aug. 19. Heavy demand for the 
tiger and rhino parts in Asia -- where they are used for reputed medical and 
sexual benefits -- has resulted in the virtual extinction of the animals. The 
U.S. sanctions -- the first time the United States has imposed trade penalties 
for environmental reasons -- will affect about $25 million a year in imports of 
coral and mollusk shell jewelry, snake, lizard and crocodile skin shoes and 
other leather goods. 
