<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY: TUSTIN'S QUALITY SYSTEMS WINS CONTRACT TO INSTALL SOFTWARE SYSTEM 
AT HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quality Systems Inc. said Wednesday that it has won a contract to develop and 
install an automated medical practice management software system at the 672-bed 
University Hospital in Augusta, Ga. Terms of the contract were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 The pact calls for the Tustin company to install customized software programs 
in one of the hospital's existing computer systems to provide the institution 
and its medical staff with real-time, interactive information processing 
capability. 
</P>
<P>
 Functions supported by the system will include diagnostic test reporting, 
treatment planning, patient monitoring, appointment scheduling, insurance 
claims processing, patient billing and accounting. 
</P>
<P>
 University Hospital is the second largest in the state of Georgia with more 
than 475 physicians on its medical staff and a monthly patient volume of about 
20,000 admissions and outpatient visits. 
</P>
<P>
 Quality Systems develops computer-based management systems for medical and 
dental group practices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
