<P>
 PacifiCare Health Systems Inc.: The company's shares jumped to record highs 
Wednesday after expectations apparently were raised in recent meetings with 
investors and analysts. 
</P>
<P>
 PacifiCare Class A shares closed at $63.75, up $7 a share, while Class B 
shares closed at $63.25, up $6.25. 
</P>
<P>
 PacifiCare Chief Executive Alan Hoops and President Wayne Lowell held a series 
of meetings Wednesday that were expected to continue today to brief the 
investment community about the company. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cypress-based health maintenance organization reported Aug. 1 that 
enrollment has increased in its managed-care plans and hospital costs per 
member had declined. 
