<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saba Petroleum Co.: The Irvine oil and gas production company reported 
second-quarter profit of $452,005, or 12 cents a share, more than double the 
$219,666, or 6 cents a share, recorded for the like period a year ago.Revenue 
declined 3%, to $2.8 million from $2.9 million. Profit for the first six months 
dropped to $95,133, or 3 cents a share, from $349,421, or 10 cents a share, for 
the same period in 1993. Revenue was down 6%, to $5.1 million from $5.4 
million. 
</P>
