<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: EMULEX POSTS $15.2-MILLION LOSS FOR YEAR ENDING JULY 3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Emulex Corp., a Costa Mesa manufacturer of software and hardware-based network 
access products, posted a loss of $15.2 million, or $2.75 a share, for the year 
ended July 3, which included $14.3 million in one-time write-downs and expenses 
attributable to the spinoff of QLogic and cost-reduction measures. That 
compares with a profit of $3.5 million, or 64 cents a share, for the previous 
fiscal year.Revenue rose to $61.6 million from $55.1 million. For the fourth 
quarter, profit was down 9% from the previous fourth quarter, to $765,000, or 
13 cents a share, from $845,000, or 15 cents a share. Earnings from 
discontinued operations represented $613,000 of the total for the fiscal 1993 
quarter. Sales increased to $18.3 million from $15 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
